screening, and 0·25 years (0·22-0·27) from all three screenings together. One 
integrated strategy (screening alcohol, tobacco, and depression with diagnostic 
assessment for all CASM conditions if any screened positive) produced 
near-maximal benefit (0·82 years [0·80-0·84]) without adding substantial 
screening burden, albeit requiring additional diagnostic assessments.
INTERPRETATION: Primary care providers for people with HIV should consider 
comprehensive diagnostic assessment of CASM conditions if one or more conditions 
screen positive.
